paragraph.text:
customer rates and
			 local charges are and will remain the primary means of paying for water service
			 and infrastructure in the United States;

since the historical default rate on water
			 and sewer bonds is 0.04 percent, the risk of default on Federal assistance
			 provided under this Act is minimal;

